I don't say this to get money back, I'm saying this because what Tesco did was something that can never happen again. Give us fair notice or my loyalty goes somewhere else. 2 stars until I get an apology. No apology so I am making 1 star. Shame Tesco.

replyContent: Hi Jane. Thanks for your feedback. It sounds like you may be on an old version of the app. I'd recommend checking for updates, or sending an email over and we'll be able to assist you from there. Thanks.

The app works ok but has some frustrations which are bad enough that I often choose to shop elsewhere on better apps. Most annoying is the convoluted checkout process every time you are just adding one small item to an existing big shop. I get that Tesco want to push impulse buys and offers at me from time to time, but every time I add a tin of beans to my shop drives me bonkers. The search is quite poor too, finding unusual items is tricky with irrelevant suggestions. Try "star anise"

No product reviews visible in the app, makes it much harder to avoid the unpleasant or poor value / quality products. If adding products from a previous order, it just adds one, not the amount you bought before, annoying if you always buy multiples eg bananas. No end date visible on the offers until you click right into the each product, meaning you can easily add things that will no longer be on offer by your delivery date. Added the current contents of my basket to the order I was editing.

Changes have made it worse. I now have favourites that I have not bought since last Xmas. And now some favourites have disappeared but when found in search show a heart for favourites. 29/11/21: buy it once, it becomes a favourite, now have delays because of "network problems". Brands being replaced by own brand. 28/1/21: Tesco now replacing brands every week. Now like Lidl/Aldi but more expensive.

For those having problems... Go into settings, and then apps and notifications, then select the Morrisons app, then storage and cache, then delete cache, and then delete data. Then go back to home and try to restart the app. If it hangs on the Morrisons logo, then close the app using square and swipe up, then open again. You'll then have to input your email and Morrisons app password again, and then life is all good... ðŸ‘

content: If it's not broken don't fix. Poor poor update when previous version only needed tweaking.

The previous app was just fine, this new version is clearly designed to be just like the website page and the paper leaflet, but this just doesn't work on a small phone screen, it's far too cluttered. There are other problems too, most of which point to a complete lack of understanding in the target user:  â€¢  Often every variant of an item will have its own separate entry. For example, if ALDI are selling children's headphones in four different colours or themes, then there will be four different entries.   â€¢  The entries under the â€œdateâ€ view are not collected together in any meaningful order, they are almost completely random. As I look at the  12th May, there is luggage, then kids t-shirts, more luggage, shoes, beach toys, more shoes, a kids clock, books, another kids clock, more t-shirts, a watch, a ball, yet another kids clock, another t-shirtâ€¦...oh, and what I was really looking for: digital luggage scales.   â€¢  Finally, where is the shopping list?? Before I could short list items and even link it to my Google calendar, now the only option I have is to order the items online. There are five ALDIs within a couple of miles of my home, so I have no interest in mail order.

Searching for various items in search panel useless,
Why doesn't this app allow fingerprint identification yet?
Always crashing, slow and generally poor. Expect so much better from one of the country's largest multiples.

With respect which fool decided we had to use a code every time we log in to the app or our account on a browser? Don't they know that not everyone gets a good signal on their mobile in their home? Please try and engage brain before coming up with new ideas.

Frustrating unclear process to change delivery slot for existing order, taking several check out attempts before it was accepted, it appeared to offer slots on a day which could not be checked out and then the whole day's slots became unavailable so had to change day! - and then feedback appeared locked up until I spotted POST in the top RH corner!

terrible app cannot use it at all anymore ðŸ˜ž I have been shopping with sainsbury's for years and was not at all happy when I couldn't log into my account eventually I got so fed up I got intouch with nectar who were most helpful and got me back in within minutes you now need the Internet explorer app and go to the sainsbury's website on that but go to nectar website first and select already member following this you should then be able to go to sainsbury's and log in OK as well Good Luck ðŸ‘

Clicking add and then being told no in a modal popup is rubbish. Love sainsburys, hate their rubbish app. Website is only just marginally less clunky.

Rubbish
When making changes and going to checkout, sents you to check alternatives then closes you down.

Really frustrating

Very slow I mean ssllowww

Not responsive after midnight... Really disappointing as the app worked well at 23:56...
Getting worse and worse.

This apps allows me to do my online shopping but it needs some serious improvement. What can't we access the product reviews? Why the recipes are only accessible using the website? Coming from Ocado, this app is miles away behind.
Difficult to use, can't use coupons on it.

Do not like your policy of no paper receipts, what if an item is wrong or of poor quality I do NOT have a printer and therefore have no proof of purchase. I am very very very upset and disappointed and want paper receipts with my on line SHOP in future this is a retrograde step for on line shoppers

However, I am amazed that at long last there is now the option to see close-ups of products - just a pity that some of the images are blurred.

replyContent:
Hi Mo MacLellan, the process to redeem at the checkout is as follows:
1. Scan your myWaitrose card - this can either be a physical card, or your digital card available within the app.
2. Go to the Voucher screen in the app, and select 'use now in-store' for the voucher you wish to redeem.
3. Scan the voucher barcode at the checkout.
